> <OLD>
>
> WHEELIE continued his taunt, "FRiends find, look behind!"  Firing another
> shot from his energon slingshot over at GRIMLOCK's olfactory receptor,
> before ducking over to the side to avoid shots, and racing over the bridge
> as the DINOBOTS chased after him, flipping over to hopefully the other side
> to make a 'NEENER, NEENER' gesture to get them to continue the chase after
> him!

<NEW>

Even as WHEELIE moved swiftly across the more or less open terrain,
GRIMLOCK was following behind, his optics dark, his teeth bared in
anger and rage as the other DINOBOTS were following behind, trying to
keep up as best they could.

Above GRIMLOCK's head SWOOP was following waiting for a chance to pick
up WHEELIE and fly him out of danger.

Then GRIMLOCK slowed as his optics flickered for a moment, "Wheelie?
What have you done to Grimlock?!?" He said in confusion as he slowed
to a walk.

"Yeah." SLAG said as he slowed as well shaking his head, "Something
differerent . . . something wrong."

The other DINOBOTS also slowed as if something were not quite right in
their own heads.

If WHEELIE did any checking he might notice that while communications
were still out, the range of his sensors was begining to grow, as if
the distortion field around this area were beginning to weaken just a
bit.

(TAG)

- Preston
